cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and image synthesis, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV sub-category. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and the proposed compositional reconstruction loss also suggest that it could belong to the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The addition of facial composition information and the focus on delicate facial structures suggest that it could also belong to the cs.GR sub-category. Finally, the wide range of applications, including digital entertainment and law enforcement, suggests that it could also belong to the cs.MM sub-category.
